1 Section 1. NRS 386.790 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 386.790 1. As provided in this title, the board of trustees of
3 any school district may furnish transportation for all resident
4 children of school age in the school district attending a public
5 school, including pupils assigned to special schools or programs
6 pursuant to NRS 388.417 to 388.469, inclusive, or 388.5251 to
7 388.5267, inclusive:
8 (a) Who are not excused from school attendance by the
9 provisions of this title; and
10 (b) Who reside within the school district at such a distance from
11 the school as to make transportation necessary and desirable.
12 2. When the board of trustees of a school district whose
13 population is less than 100,000 furnishes transportation for pupils
14 attending public schools pursuant to subsection 1, the board may
15 also provide transportation for all resident children of school age in
16 the school district attending private schools not operated for profit,
17 over bus routes established for pupils attending public schools. If
18 such transportation is provided, the pupils attending such private
19 schools must be transported, if space is available, to and from the
20 points on the established routes nearest to the schools which they
21 attend.
22 3. The board of trustees of any school district may:
23 (a) Establish bus routes.
24 (b) Make regulations governing the conduct of pupils while
25 being transported.
26 (c) For the safety of pupils being transported, govern the
27 conduct of drivers by making and enforcing regulations not
28 inconsistent with regulations of the State Board of Education or with
29 law.
30 4. If the board of trustees of a school district furnishes
31 transportation pursuant to this section, the board of trustees may
32 elect not to provide transportation to pupils who attend a public
33 school outside the zone of attendance that the pupil is otherwise
34 required to attend pursuant to paragraph (f) of subsection 2 of
35 NRS 388.040.
