30 (a) Establish an application process through which a pupil
31 may request to attend, pursuant to paragraph (f) of subsection 2, a
32 public school outside the zone of attendance that the pupil is
33 otherwise required to attend. The process must:
34 (1) Include an annual deadline by which a pupil must
35 submit the application to the board of trustees of the school district
36 in which the school the pupil requests to attend is located; and
37 (2) Provide for the notification of a pupil and his or her
38 parent or legal guardian, and the principals of the schools
39 involved in the transfer of the pupil, if an application is approved.
40 (b) Ensure that any application developed pursuant to
41 paragraph (a) is made available in the five most common
42 languages other than English primarily spoken in households in
43 this State as determined by the Superintendent of Public
44 Instruction, which may include, without limitation, Spanish and
45 Tagalog.
